This is the "official" documentation of Web Services API. If you are running
juicer with the example configuration file, the web services are running at
http://localhost:8811/

The web services are broken into three main groups of functionality, delimited
by a prefix in the url path, they are:
1. Repositories
2. Packages
3. Consumers
This document is organized by these groups as sections.


1. Repositories ===============================================================

Function: List all available repositories
URL Path: /repositories/
Method:   GET
Body:     None
Return:   JSON encoded list of repositories

Function: Create a new repository
URL Path: /repositories/new/
Method:   POST
Body:     JSON encoded repository information
Return:   JSON encoded repository information on success

Function: Get information on a specific repository
URL Path: /repositories/<integer id>/
Method:   GET
Body:     None
Return:   JSON encoded repository information

Function: Update repository information
URL Path: /repositories/<integer id>/
Method:   POST
Body:     JSON encoded repository information
Return:   JSON encoded True on success

Function: Delete a repository
URL Path: /repositories/<integer id>/
Method:   DELETE
Body:     None
Return:   JSON encoded True on success

Function: List all packages in a repository
URL Path: /repositories/<integer id>/list/
Method:   GET
Body:     None
Return:   JSON encoded list of packages in the repository

Function: Sync a repository
URL Path: /repositories/<integer id>/sync/
Method:   GET
Body:     None
Return:   JSON encoded True on success


